{"Reviews": [{"Content": "Very good hotel for the price This is a very good hotel for the price I paid (45 euros per night).It is situated in a quiet suburb, at a couple of steps of the end of a U-Bahn (Metro) line. The trip to the Berlin downtown takes about 35 minutes, but you don't have to change train. All the rooms are situated on the first floor.The room was very clean and comfortable, in the german way. There is a 24 hours reception with friendly staff.A very good place to stay if you're not required to be in the center of Berlin.", "Date": "Nov 19, 2006", "ReviewID": "UR800184858", "Ratings": {"Service": "4", "Business service": "-1", "Cleanliness": "5", "Check in / front desk": "4", "Overall": "5", "Value": "4", "Rooms": "5", "Location": "3"}, "Author": "MeepMeepGVA"}, {"Content": "Budget Value My wife and son and I stayed in this hotel for two nights. It's at the end of the line on the train, way out in the suburbs, maybe a block from the train station. The hotel is only the third floor of the building. We had a family room facing the street. Windows opened fine, as there is no air conditioner (normal in Europe). I was a hot weekend. We couldn't take a cold shower, as the shower only had hot water comng out! Large clean bathroom. Bunk beds and a dbl bed in our room with a 9 inch color TV that worked fine, but small.Breakfast was good, with some hot items. Hotel had mostly families while we were there.Too far out of town if visiting Berlin. Pick something closer.", "Date": "Jul 17, 2005", "ReviewID": "UR747751257", "Ratings": {"Service": "3", "Business service": "-1", "Cleanliness": "3", "Check in / front desk": "-1", "Overall": "3", "Value": "3", "Rooms": "2", "Location": "-1"}, "Author": "rhut01"}, {"Content": "HEP war super!   showReview(8398750, 'full');", "Date": "Aug 12, 2007", "ReviewID": "UR891467531", "Ratings": {"Service": "4", "Business service": "3", "Cleanliness": "4", "Check in / front desk": "5", "Overall": "4", "Value": "5", "Rooms": "4", "L